    <p>If you are using a contributed Drupal theme, the best way to make your changes sub-theme.</p>
<p>So, if you want to modify Bartik (the default theme) or any theme you find on Drupal.org, we recommend a sub-theme. Using a sub-theme means you can safely update the underlying theme without losing any of your changes.</p>
<p>These two videos are a beginners guide to creating and using a sub-theme.</p>
